About
=====

Zacacia is a web frontend to manage an OpenLDAP direcory.
This OpenLDAP directory can be used with Zarafa Collaborative Platform - ZCP - (http://www.zarafa.com/)


Requirements
============

Zacacia is written in PHP5 and use the symfony, an open-source PHP web framework (http://www.symfony-project.org/)

 - Debian Linux >= 5.0
 - Apache 2 (apt-get install apache2-mpm-prefork)
 - PHP5 (apt-get install libapache2-mod-php5)
 - OpenLDAP (apt-get install slapd)
 - LDAP module for PHP5 (apt-get install php5-ldap) 


Installation
============

 - Apache
untar the zacacia.tar.gz in /opt/WebSites/
create link in /etc/apache2/site-enable/
restart apache

 - OpenLDAP
 /etc/init.d/slapd stop
 cp /opt/WebSites/Zacacia/install/openldap/ldap/slapd.conf /etc/ldap/slapd.conf
 cp /opt/WebSites/Zacacia/install/openldap/ldap/schema/zacacia.schema /etc/ldap/schema/
 cp /usr/share/doc/zarafa/zarafa.schema /etc/ldap/schema/
 rm -f /var/lib/ldap/*
 slapadd -f /etc/ldap/slapd.conf -l /opt/WebSites/Zacacia/install/openldap/zacacia.ldif
 chown -R openldap:openldap /var/lib/ldap
 /etc/init.d/slapd start


